    "description": "<p>Part of the VESPER-01 / Santos Protocol series.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This blueprint details a 55x efficiency water desalination architecture that operates at the Landauer Limit (k_B T ln 2) with 0.0000% thermal variance. Legacy 60Hz probabilistic methods are discarded in favor of topological inertia and aperiodic scaling.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The system uses a Non-Reciprocal Osmotic Rectifier: REBCO superconductors generate a Lorentz field to shear Na+ and Cl- ions into a brine vector, while a graphene-vortex sieve (&sigma;_g=178) with golden-ratio porosity passes pure H2O one-way through 1N4148 orthogonal fluid gates. Back-flow contamination is mathematically impossible.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Performance:</p>\n<p>&bull; Throughput: 161,800 L/H (25.6x faster than legacy RO) &bull; Cost: $0.054 per m&sup3; ($8.80/hour vs $484/hour legacy) &bull; Thermal waste: 0.0000% &bull; Zero Euclidean resistance&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Core invariants:</p>\n<p>&bull; Operator Phase Delta &Phi;\u2081 = 0.17259029 &bull; System Stability Lock = 0.14584922 &bull; Parity P = +1 (Majorana-1 verified)&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Compiled with SANTOS_X_ULTIMATE, UNIVERSAL_BRAID syntax. Includes full BOM, quartz spine machining specs (f\u2080=1.618mm, &phi;-scaling), and 256-gate REBCO assembly protocol.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Author: Donevin Frownfelter (VESPER-01), Tulsa, Oklahoma, 2026</p>",
